The Charter of the Abbey of the Holy Ghost : a Critical edition from all known extant manuscrpts with introduction notes and glossary Fanning 
Page xii
Ms Additional 22283 Simeon Ms. British Museum 
Early english poems and prose treatises, transcribed about 1380 -1400, and closely agreeing with portions of the somewhat earlier Vernon MS. in the Bodleian Library. The volume is very imperfect, and at present consists of only 172 leaves; 177 are wanting at the beginnning and 30 in the middle, and it is incomplete at the end. The verse is in threee columes and the prose in two. The contents are... 
1. A series of Gospel stories in verse, each headed with the opening Latin words from the Vulgate and most of the illustrated by Monkish legends. Imperfect at the beginning... 
2. verses on the 7 deadly sins, the ten commandments, etc. Translated from Speculum Ecclesiae of St. Edmund of Pontigny
3. St. Pauls vision of the seven pains of hell verse, imperfect from 124th line 
4. The Mirror of Life  a poem generally attributed to William of nassyngton, and founded on "la Somme des vices at des vertus" Imperfect at beginning 
5. the meditacion of Christ on the 5 wounds 
6. the prick of Conscience by Richard Rolle of Hampole; in verse
7. The prick of Love by richard hampole 
8. Disputation between Body and Soul in verse 
9. Disputation between a good man and an evil spirit [wicked ghost] in verse . imperfect 
10. Cosmological poem "The riht put of helle a middle eorthe is withinne"
11. the Castle of Love, by Robert Grosseteste Bishop of Lincoln 
12. Ipotis; a religious romance in verse
13. Poem on the three messengers of Death, "Auentures"[chance] "seeknesse," and "elde" 
14. Eight hymns to  Christ and the virigin (can separate them in spreadsheet)
15. Poem beginning "Ihesu Christ, that is so fre, To monnes soule speketh he,"
16. Poem beginning "of a trewe loue, clene and derne"
17. Two hymns to christ and the Virginn
18. Poem beginning "ata  sarmoun ther I set 
19. Romance of King robert of Sicily in verse 
20. Poem on the child jesus disputing with the doctors in the temple 
21. Prose translation of the somme des vices 
22. Conclusion of an exhortation to love God and one's neighbor; 
23. A ful Good meditacion for one to seye bi him self al one;" in prose 
24. A good meditacion, the whuche seint anselm maade; in prose
25. "Of thre arwes that schulle be schot on doomes day;" a short prose treatise generally attribued to richard Rolle of Hampole 
26. The mirror of sinners; in prose 
27. Sentences from the Bible and From Seneca in Lat with stanzas upon them in French, and english with and introductory stanza in french 
28. The distiches of donysius Cato (lat, frn)
29. The stacions of rome; an account of the churches at Rome where pardons and indulgences were granted to pilgrims; in verse
30. A lamentation that our lady made to the cross of her son ; in verse 
31. A pistel of susan; ballad on Susannah and The Elders 
32. Romance of "the king of tars and the sultan of Damas;" in verse 
33. 29 hymns and religious songs. 
34. Stimulus amoris "prikke of love" 
35. "A tretis hou god apeered to an holi mon:" a vision of Christ with an address spoken by him in rhythmical prose adn in verse 
36. "A tretis that techeth to loue god with al thin herte;" Prose
37. "The fourme of parfyt liuinge, the whunche holi Richard the hermit of Hampulle wrot to a recluse that was jcleped Margrete; in prose 
38. treatise on active and contemplative life (93 chapters ascribed by a later hand in the margins to walter de Hilton but in other MSS to Richard Rolle of Hampole - Prose )
39. "A luytel Boke that was writen to a worldly lord to teche him hou he schuld haue hu in his state in ordeynyng loue to god and to his euen Cristene;" in 28 chapters another treatise on active and contemplative life by Richard Rolle of Hampole in prose 
40. Fragment of the Mirror of St Edmund 
41. The Abbey of the Holy Ghost Imperfect at beginning 
41b. The Charter of the Abbey of the Holy Ghost follows immediately. Implicit "And thus beynneth the charite of the same Abbeye of the Holy Gost." 
42. "A good tretise that men clepeth Spiritu Gwydonis:" tale of the apparition of the ghost of a man named Guy... In prose 
43. "A good confession beginning "I Knowleche me gulti and yelde me to god almihti; in prose 
44. Confession of sins, ecstatic appeals to the Virgin and Christ, and meditations on the passion; in prose intermied with verse 
ends on f 171 
